Ecosystems are one of the basic units of ecology: combinations of organisms and inorganic environmental features that interact with each other and are found in a given time and place. A forest on the side of a mountain, a tree in that forest, or a leaf on that tree are all examples of ecosystems. Besides obvious differences in size, they all share key traits. Each of them comprises 
\f2\i trophic interactions
